Azimuth adjusted, signal at -75 dB—adequate, I suppose. Now tweak the elevation. The dish needs to lock onto a pulsar with a period of 1.391 seconds—PSR B1919+21, if I recall correctly. Adjust the elevation dial until the signal peaks; you’re aiming for -60 dB or better. I once misaligned the dish and we ended up in a nebula that smelled like Lister’s socks. Let’s not repeat that.